esently run by banks.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Banks charge a fee every time they facilitate a cross-border financial transaction, making this a highly profitable sector.<br>Deploying blockchain in cloud banking will eliminate these fees and reduce the time taken to transmit money from one person to the next.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, the public transaction ledger provides a cheap and secure way to complete payments, which does away with the need for third-party verifications.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"2-better-clearance-and-settlement-systems\"><\/span>2. Better Clearance and Settlement Systems<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A typical bank transfer takes up to three days to complete. The reason for this has to do with how the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.finextra.com\/blogposting\/18474\/financial-infrastructure-the-fintech-way\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">payments solution and financial infrastructure<\/a> are built.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The added time is a pain to the client and makes it challenging for banks to move money from one branch to another or from one account to the next.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Currently, a simple payment from one account to another needs to pass through a complicated network of intermediaries before arriving at its final destination.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The distributed ledger technologies can assist in reducing operational costs while bringing its users closer to enjoying real-time financial transactions between banks.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"3-fundraising-for-startups-during-icos\"><\/span>3. Fundraising for Startups During ICOs<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Using the existing financial services framework to <a href=\"https:\/\/pitchbook.com\/blog\/what-is-venture-capital\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">raise money through venture capital<\/a> is a laborious process.<br>An entrepreneur will need to prepare decks and meet with partners requiring them to sit through a series of countless meetings as they negotiate over equity and valuation.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>They have to do all this with the hope of getting to exchange a portion of the company for funding. In contrast, some firms are using ICOs powered by a distributed ledger to raise funds.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Initial coin offerings are helping entrepreneurs experiment with a new financing model that unbundles access to money from normal capital raising activities.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"4-blockchain-in-cloud-banking-can-help-to-create-interoperable-securities\"><\/span>4. Blockchain In Cloud Banking Can Help to Create Interoperable Securities<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To buy or sell assets such as commodities, debt, and stocks using a digital payment system, you need to have a way of tracking who owns what item.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Financial markets operating today use a complex network of clearinghouses, brokers, central security depositories and exchanges to achieve this fete.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>All these parties work using an outdated financial services system that\u2019s slow and prone to errors.<br>The problem becomes compounded when users attempt to complete a financial transaction using an online payment method.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Applying AI in securities will help <a href=\"https:\/\/corporatefinanceinstitute.com\/resources\/knowledge\/finance\/security\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">tokenize traditional securities<\/a> such as bonds, stocks, and other alternative assets.<br>It will place all of them on a public distributed ledger to create more efficiency and allow for the emergence of interoperable capital markets.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"5-using-blockchain-in-cloud-banking-to-underwrite-loans-and-credit-facilities\"><\/span>5. Using Blockchain in Cloud Banking to Underwrite Loans and Credit Facilities<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Traditional banks and payment processors use a credit reporting system to underwrite loans and credit facilities.<br>Digital ledger technology helps to open up an opportunity for peer-to-peer loans.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Normally, banks require loan applicants to fill a form when applying for a loan. They evaluate each applicant\u2019s creditworthiness by looking at factors such as:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Homeownership status<\/li><li>Credit score<\/li><li>Debt-to-income ratio<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>They can get this information by requesting a credit report from a credit agency. The use of such a centralized system can prove hostile to consumers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Adopting <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ey.com\/en_uk\/banking-capital-markets\/uk-banking-public-cloud-adoption-banks-must-think-big-to-transform\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">cloud banking technologies<\/a> based on DLT technologies can eliminate the need for gatekeepers in the loans and mortgage industry.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Implementation of a public transaction ledger can assist in making it easier for individuals to borrow money. It can also help reduce the interest rates charged by financial services firms.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" src=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Application-of-AI-and-Cryptographic-Ledger-to-Cloud-Banking.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1051\" srcset=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Application-of-AI-and-Cryptographic-Ledger-to-Cloud-Banking.jpg 800w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Application-of-AI-and-Cryptographic-Ledger-to-Cloud-Banking-300x150.jpg 300w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Application-of-AI-and-Cryptographic-Ledger-to-Cloud-Banking-768x384.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"6-increased-transparency-and-security-in-trade-finance\"><\/span>6. Increased Transparency and Security in Trade Finance<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Trade finance exists to ensure that importers and exporters can engage in global trade, lessen risks, and extend credit.<br>It plays a crucial role in the global financial system, despite operating on old-fashioned, written documentation instead of an online digital payment system.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Artificial intelligence and cryptographic ledgers present an opportunity to simplify and streamline the complex world of payment processing.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Its implementation can save financiers, importers, and exporters billions of dollars each year.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Furthermore, by replacing the tiresome paper-heavy bills used in the lading process, this technology can create trust and transparency among global trade parties.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"7-fraud-prevention-and-customized-kyc-for-payment-processors\"><\/span>7. Fraud Prevention and Customized KYC for Payment Processors<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition to processing payments and clearing financial transactions, banks also need to onboard new clients, ensure their information is in order, and verify their identity.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The entire process is known as <a href=\"https:\/\/www.electronicid.eu\/en\/blog\/post\/kyc-know-your-customer-means\/en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\u201cknow your customer\u201d<\/a> (KYC).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Payment processing companies can spend up to ninety days executing KYC proceedings, causing some patients to become impatient and end their business relationships.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>By storing client information on decentralized blocks, DLT in cloud banking can make it easier for banks to share information with payment processors and guarantee its security.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The deployment of blockchain in cloud banking provides untrusted part